Key Takeaways


Password and lockout policies belong in the Default Domain Policy — not a custom GPO
gpresult /r /scope computer is the correct way to verify which GPOs are applying at the machine level — running it without /scope computer shows user-level policies only
Get-ADUser in PowerShell is useful for checking BadLogonCount and LockedOut status when troubleshooting lockout policies
gpupdate /force needs to run on the client machine, not just the DC, to pull down policy changes immediately
